data.description: If Thomas Edison hadn't figured out the light bulb, it would have taken about 1800 candles to light this HUGE 3220 square foot-5 bedroom, 3 bath masterpiece. Thankfully he did and you just have to flip a switch to enjoy all of the amenities of this great home.  Welcoming 2-story entryway, tons of custom arches throughout, formal dining room for entertaining, formal and intimate living rooms, hardwood floors, spacious kitchen w/TONS of cabinetry, counter space and large center island, window-wrapped breakfast room built for enjoying a quiet cup of coffee, bedroom on main, sunlit master suite w/tray ceiling, 14x10 closet and private bath w/double sinks, sep shower and Jacuzzi tub, big bedrooms and wonderfully situated rec room just waiting for your next party.  Plus, enjoy a lovely covered front porch and inviting patio in rear.
